OllamaURL = Ollama Server URL
OllamaURLDesc = Your local Ollama server URL (e.g. http://localhost:11434/api)
OllamaURLRequired = Ollama server URL is required
OllamaTimeout = HTTP timeout
OllamaTimeoutDesc = Maximum time (in seconds) to wait for a single Ollama response. The default (300s) covers most self-hosted setups. Raise it if you run a large model on CPU and see cURL timeout errors. The NeuronAI library defaults to 60s, which is often too short.
CloudHttpTimeout = Cloud providers HTTP timeout
CloudHttpTimeoutDesc = Maximum time (in seconds) to wait for a response from cloud providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Mistral, Gemini). The default (300s) covers long conversations with large context and many tools. The NeuronAI library defaults to 60s, which triggers "cURL error 28: Operation timed out" errors on loaded threads. Only lower it if you want to fail faster on network issues.
ToolMaxRuns = Max tool invocations per turn
ToolMaxRunsDesc = Maximum number of times a single tool may be invoked within one chat turn before the agent raises a quota error. Increase for complex analyses (e.g. 25-50 for multi-query SQL explorations). The NeuronAI library defaults to 10, too low for many legitimate workloads. Range: 5-100, default: 25. The anti-loop protection (3 consecutive identical calls) stays active regardless of this value.
OllamaNumCtx = Context window (num_ctx)
OllamaNumCtxDesc = Number of tokens the Ollama model can process in a single request (input + output combined). Ollama's built-in default (2048-4096) is too small for the Dalfred tool catalogue and causes truncated prompts. 16384 fits in 8-12 GB VRAM for a 7B model and is a safe default. Set to 0 to disable and use Ollama's built-in default (not recommended).
Seconds = seconds
OllamaModelPlaceholder = Model name (e.g. llama3, mistral, codellama...)
CustomModelPlaceholder = Enter model name (e.g. claude-sonnet-4-5-20250514)...
OtherCustomModel = Other (custom model)
